I will retrieve information about Paul Manafort first, as he is widely known for his role as a senior member of Trump's campaign.
steps.observation: Paul John Manafort Jr. (born April 1, 1949) is an American lawyer, lobbyist and political consultant.  He joined Donald Trump's presidential campaign team in March 2016 and served as campaign manager from June to August 2016.  He was previously an adviser to the U.S. presidential campaigns of Republicans Gerald Ford, Ronald Reagan, George H. W. Bush, and Bob Dole.  In 1980 Manafort co-founded the Washington, D.C.-based lobbying firm Black, Manafort & Stone, along with principals Charles R. Black Jr., and Roger J. Stone.  In 1984 it was renamed Black, Manafort, Stone and Kelly (BMSK) & associates, after Peter G. Kelly was recruited.
